article.headline: Southern Cal 62, Long Beach St. 44
article.story: LOS ANGELES -- Eric Wise scored 10 points and grabbed 12 rebounds and Ari Stewart and J.T. Terrell each scored 10 points as USC defeated Long Beach State, 62-44 Tuesday night. Stewart led a strong night for USC's bench, which outscored Long Beach's reserves, 23-3. Dewayne Dedmon had eight points and 10 rebounds for the Trojans, who recorded only their third 2-0 start in the past 11 years. Mike Caffey led the 49ers (1-1) with 17 points and James Ennis added 13. Long Beach State shot only 29 percent and had 18 turnovers. USC went on a 23-4 run after Long Beach State tied it at 35 early in the second half. Dedmon capped the run with a tip-in of Terrell's miss, then dunked an alley-oop pass from Byron Wesley for a 58-39 lead.
